# Language: commits and technical messages

## Prohibited in Git commits (non-negotiable)

- **Never** add `--trailer "Made-with: Cursor"` or **any** Git trailer that names **Cursor**, **AI**, **LLM**, **Copilot**, or similar tooling as author/source.
- **Never** put Cursor/AI attribution in commit **subject**, **body**, **trailers**, or **footers** unless the human maintainer explicitly asks for a specific line for their own reasons.
- Commits must read like normal engineering history: what changed and why, period.

## Required style

- **Git commits**: subject and body in **English** (imperative mood, conventional style when useful: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, etc.).
- **Pull requests**: title and description in **English**.
- **Branch names**: English (`feature/kafka-leaderboard`, `fix/submit-timer`).
- **Code comments** in new code: **English** unless the codebase already uses another language in that file (stay consistent per file).
- **User-facing UI copy** for API Arena: follow existing product language (nav/chrome in English per brand rules); Spanish only when explicitly requested for a specific screen.

This does not require translating existing Spanish-only docs unless someone is editing them for other reasons.
